## Configuration Persistence

### Config File
- **Path**: `.cursor/config/saved_config.json`
- **Purpose**: Store validated configuration after successful API execution

### JSON Structure
Config file stores an **array** of configurations for each API type, preserving history of all working configs:
```json
{
  "gcnv": [
    {
      "endpoint_type": "CCFE|Proxy",
      "base_url": "...",
      "project_id": "...",
      "project_number": "...",
      "region": "...",
      "vpc_network": "...",
      "saved_at": "ISO timestamp"
    }
  ],
  "ontap": [
    {
      "endpoint_type": "CCFE|Proxy",
      "base_url": "...",
      "project_id": "...",
      "project_number": "...",
      "zone": "...",
      "region": "...",
      "storage_pool": "...",
      "pool_id": "...",
      "svm_name": "...",
      "saved_at": "ISO timestamp"
    }
  ]
}
```
- Newest configs are added to the **beginning** of the array
- Old configs are preserved for user selection

### Rules
- Only save config after **successful** API execution (HTTP 2xx response)
- **Never overwrite** existing configs - always append to history
- Newest configs appear first in the array
- Include timestamp (`saved_at`) for user reference
- Never auto-delete saved configs

